<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870917-0147 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Columbia Gas System Inc.</HL><DD> 09/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CG </IN><TEXT>   Columbia Gas System Inc., Wilmington, Del., said it formed a partnership with two other companies to build and operate cogeneration plants.    Columbia, a natural gas concern, said it would contribute an equity investment of $6 million and loans of $14 million to the partnership. The other participants are Atlantic City Electric Co., Pleasantville, N.J., and On-Site Power Systems, Edison, N.J. The total investment in the partnership wasn't disclosed.    The new partnership, Cogeneration Partners of America, has plans for at least eight plants designed to produce electricity and usable thermal energy from a single fuel source. </TEXT></DOC>